curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/13366' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM8603", "table_name": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION", "content": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION  The SGM8603 (single with shutdown) is a low voltage,  low noise and low power operational amplifier, which  can operate from 2.1V to 5.5V single supply, while  consuming only 1.1mA quiescent current at 5V. The  supply current is less than 1μA in power-down mode.  The SGM8603 features a 4.9mV maximum input offset  voltage. The minimum input common mode voltage is  within 0.1V below the negative rail, and the output  swing is rail-to-rail with heavy loads. It exhibits a high  gain-bandwidth product of 11MHz and a slew rate of  8.5V/μs. These specifications make the operational  amplifier appropriate for various applications.  The SGM8603 is available in a Green TDFN-2×2-6L  package. It is specified over the extended -40℃ to  +125℃ industrial temperature range.      "}'
curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/13367' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM8603", "table_name": "FEATURES", "content": "FEATURES  ● Input Offset Voltage: 1.1mV (TYP)  ● High Gain-Bandwidth Product: 11MHz  ● High Slew Rate: 8.5V/μs  ● Settling Time to 0.1% with 2V Step: 0.21μs  ● Overload Recovery Time: 0.6μs  ● Low Noise: 8.5nV/√Hz at 10kHz  ● Rail-to-Rail Input and Output  ● Supply Voltage Range: 2.1V to 5.5V  ● Input Voltage Range: -0.1V to 5.6V with VS = 5.5V  ● Low Power:  1.1mA (TYP) Supply Current  Less than 1μA when Disabled  ● -40℃ to +125℃ Operating Temperature Range  ● Available in a Green TDFN-2×2-6L Package      "}'
